		<section class="comparison-hero section">
			<div class="container">
				<nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb">
					<ol>
						<li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
						<li><a href="/eor">EOR Services</a></li>
						<li>EOR Canada vs Mexico</li>
					</ol>
				</nav>
				<div class="hero-content">
					<h1>EOR Canada vs EOR Mexico: Complete Comparison</h1>
					<p class="hero-subtitle">Should you use an Employer of Record service in Canada or Mexico? Compare costs, talent quality, time zones, compliance, and cultural factors to make the best decision for your business.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="quick-comparison section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="section-header">
					<h2>Quick Comparison</h2>
					<p>Key differences at a glance</p>
				</div>
				<div class="comparison-table-wrapper">
					<table class="comparison-table">
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Factor</th>
								<th>EOR Canada</th>
								<th>EOR Mexico</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Cost Savings</strong></td>
								<td>10-40% vs. U.S.</td>
								<td>50-70% vs. U.S.</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Time Zone</strong></td>
								<td>Same or 1-3 hours</td>
								<td>1-3 hours difference</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Language</strong></td>
								<td>English & French</td>
								<td>Spanish (English in tech)</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Talent Quality</strong></td>
								<td>Very High</td>
								<td>High (growing)</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Compliance Complexity</strong></td>
								<td>Moderate</td>
								<td>High</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Cultural Alignment</strong></td>
								<td>Very High</td>
								<td>Moderate</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Legal System</strong></td>
								<td>Common law (similar to U.S.)</td>
								<td>Civil law (different)</td>
							</tr>
							<tr>
								<td><strong>Best For</strong></td>
								<td>Quality, alignment, ease</td>
								<td>Maximum cost savings</td>
							</tr>
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="detailed-comparison section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="section-header">
					<h2>Detailed Comparison</h2>
					<p>In-depth analysis of each option</p>
				</div>
				<div class="comparison-grid">
					<div class="comparison-card">
						<h3>Cost Comparison</h3>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Canada</h4>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Salary Savings:</strong> 10-40% vs. U.S. equivalents</li>
								<li><strong>Junior Developer:</strong> $50,000-$70,000 USD</li>
								<li><strong>Senior Developer:</strong> $70,000-$120,000 USD</li>
								<li><strong>EOR Service Fee:</strong> $499-$1,500/month</li>
								<li><strong>Total Cost:</strong> Moderate savings with high quality</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Mexico</h4>
							<ul>
								<li><strong>Salary Savings:</strong> 50-70% vs. U.S. equivalents</li>
								<li><strong>Junior Developer:</strong> $20,000-$35,000 USD</li>
								<li><strong>Senior Developer:</strong> $40,000-$70,000 USD</li>
								<li><strong>EOR Service Fee:</strong> Similar range</li>
								<li><strong>Total Cost:</strong> Maximum savings</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<p class="cost-note"><strong>Break-even consideration:</strong> While Mexico offers greater cost savings, Canada provides better cultural alignment, time zone overlap, and legal system familiarity.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="comparison-card">
						<h3>Talent Quality & Education</h3>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Canada</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Highly educated workforce</li>
								<li>Strong university system</li>
								<li>Excellent English proficiency</li>
								<li>Proven track record in tech</li>
								<li>High-quality code standards</li>
								<li>Strong problem-solving skills</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Mexico</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Growing tech talent pool</li>
								<li>Strong engineering programs</li>
								<li>English proficiency varies</li>
								<li>Rapidly improving tech sector</li>
								<li>Good technical skills</li>
								<li>Cost-effective talent</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<p class="talent-note"><strong>Quality Factor:</strong> Canada generally offers more consistent quality and experience, while Mexico offers excellent value for the cost.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="comparison-card">
						<h3>Time Zone & Collaboration</h3>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Canada</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Same time zones as most U.S. states</li>
								<li>Maximum 3-hour difference</li>
								<li>Easy real-time collaboration</li>
								<li>Overlapping work hours</li>
								<li>No significant time zone challenges</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Mexico</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>1-3 hours difference from U.S.</li>
								<li>Good overlap for most U.S. time zones</li>
								<li>Reasonable collaboration windows</li>
								<li>Some scheduling coordination needed</li>
								<li>Generally manageable</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<p class="timezone-note"><strong>Collaboration Impact:</strong> Canada offers better time zone alignment, making real-time collaboration easier and more natural.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="comparison-card">
						<h3>Language & Communication</h3>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Canada</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>English as primary language</li>
								<li>French available (bilingual advantage)</li>
								<li>Native-level English proficiency</li>
								<li>No language barriers</li>
								<li>Seamless communication</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Mexico</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Spanish as primary language</li>
								<li>English common in tech sector</li>
								<li>English proficiency varies</li>
								<li>Some language barriers possible</li>
								<li>Communication may require translation</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<p class="language-note"><strong>Communication Factor:</strong> Canada offers native-level English communication, eliminating language barriers entirely.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="comparison-card">
						<h3>Compliance & Legal Complexity</h3>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Canada</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Common law system (similar to U.S.)</li>
								<li>Familiar legal framework</li>
								<li>Moderate compliance complexity</li>
								<li>Well-established EOR market</li>
								<li>Clear employment standards</li>
								<li>Predictable compliance requirements</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Mexico</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Civil law system (different from U.S.)</li>
								<li>Less familiar legal framework</li>
								<li>Higher compliance complexity</li>
								<li>Evolving EOR market</li>
								<li>Complex labor laws</li>
								<li>More compliance variables</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<p class="compliance-note"><strong>Compliance Factor:</strong> Canada's legal system is more similar to the U.S., making compliance more straightforward and predictable.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="comparison-card">
						<h3>Cultural Alignment</h3>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Canada</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Very similar business culture</li>
								<li>Similar work styles and expectations</li>
								<li>Strong cultural alignment</li>
								<li>Easy team integration</li>
								<li>Minimal cultural barriers</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<div class="comparison-item">
							<h4>EOR Mexico</h4>
							<ul>
								<li>Different business culture</li>
								<li>Different work styles</li>
								<li>Moderate cultural alignment</li>
								<li>Some cultural adaptation needed</li>
								<li>Cultural differences to navigate</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
						<p class="cultural-note"><strong>Cultural Factor:</strong> Canada offers stronger cultural alignment, making team integration and collaboration more seamless.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="when-to-choose section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="section-header">
					<h2>When to Choose Each Option</h2>
					<p>Decision factors to consider</p>
				</div>
				<div class="choice-grid">
					<div class="choice-card">
						<h3>Choose EOR Canada If:</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Quality and cultural alignment are priorities</li>
							<li>You need seamless communication (English)</li>
							<li>You want maximum time zone overlap</li>
							<li>You prefer familiar legal systems</li>
							<li>You want easier team integration</li>
							<li>You value predictability and stability</li>
							<li>10-40% cost savings is sufficient</li>
							<li>You want to minimize cultural barriers</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="choice-card">
						<h3>Choose EOR Mexico If:</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Maximum cost savings is the priority</li>
							<li>50-70% cost reduction is needed</li>
							<li>You can manage language differences</li>
							<li>You're comfortable with different legal systems</li>
							<li>You can adapt to cultural differences</li>
							<li>You have experience with Latin American markets</li>
							<li>You need to maximize budget efficiency</li>
							<li>You can invest in cultural integration</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="statistics section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="section-header">
					<h2>Key Statistics</h2>
					<p>Data-driven insights</p>
				</div>
				<div class="stats-grid">
					<div class="stat-card">
						<h3>Cost Savings</h3>
						<p class="stat-number">10-40%</p>
						<p class="stat-label">Canada</p>
						<p class="stat-compare">vs. 50-70% in Mexico</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stat-card">
						<h3>Time Zone Overlap</h3>
						<p class="stat-number">Same/1-3hr</p>
						<p class="stat-label">Canada</p>
						<p class="stat-compare">vs. 1-3hr in Mexico</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stat-card">
						<h3>Language Barrier</h3>
						<p class="stat-number">None</p>
						<p class="stat-label">Canada</p>
						<p class="stat-compare">vs. Some in Mexico</p>
					</div>
					<div class="stat-card">
						<h3>Cultural Alignment</h3>
						<p class="stat-number">Very High</p>
						<p class="stat-label">Canada</p>
						<p class="stat-compare">vs. Moderate in Mexico</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="cta section">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="cta-content">
					<h2>Need Help Deciding?</h2>
					<p>Our team specializes in Canadian EOR services and can help you evaluate whether Canada or Mexico is the better fit for your specific needs.</p>
					<a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Get a Free Consultation</a>
					<p class="cta-email">Or email us at <a href="mailto:marc@infradevconsulting.com">marc@infradevconsulting.com</a></p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</Layout>

